revision.text:
The '''Abuja Declarations and Frameworks for Action on Roll Back Malaria''' was a pledge made in 2001 by members of the [[African Union]] during a conference in [[Abuja, Nigeria]]. In it, the member nations pledged to increase their health budget to at least 15% of the state´s annual budget, and requested Western donor countries to increase their support. Tracking the progress of the efforts, the [[World Health Organization]] reported in 2010 that only one African country had reached that target, while 26 had increased health expenditures and 11 had reduced it. Nine others had not had a noticeable negative or positive trend.<ref>http://www.who.int/healthsystems/publications/abuja_declaration/en/</ref>
