{{Infobox award | name = Good Food Awards | subheader = | current_awards = [[beer]], [[charcuterie]], [[cheese]], [[chocolate]], [[cider]], [[coffee]], [[confections]], [[fish preservation|fish]], [[honey]], [[cooking oils|oils]], [[pantry]], [[pickled cucumber|pickles]], [[preserves]], [[distilled beverage|spirits]] | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | description = | sponsor = Good Food Retailers Collaborative | date = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location = [[San Francisco]], [[California]] | country = [[United States of America]] | presenter = | reward = | year = 2011 | year2 = | holder = | website = {{URL|www.goodfoodawards.org}} | image2 = | image2size = | alt2 = | caption2 = | previous = | main = | next = }}
The '''Good Food Awards''' or '''GFAs''' is an annual award competition for outstanding American craft food producers and the farmers who provide their ingredients. Created by the [http://goodfoodawards.org Good Food Foundation] (formerly Seedling Projects), the Good Food Awards celebrate the kind of food we all want to eat: tasty, authentic and responsibly produced. An annual Awards Ceremony and Marketplace is held to honor the Good Food Award recipients who push their industries towards craftsmanship and sustainability while enhancing our agricultural landscape and building strong communities.<ref name=Thelin>{{cite web|last1=Thelin|first1=Emily|title=Good Food Awards bestow accolades on those who make the cut|url=http://www.sfgate.com/food/article/Good-Food-Awards-bestow-accolades-on-those-who-5991068.php|website=San Francisco Gate|accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=Lucchesi>{{cite web|last1=Lucchesi|first1=Paolo|title=2015 Good Food Awards winners announced|url=http://insidescoopsf.sfgate.com/blog/2015/01/09/2015-good-food-awards-winners-announced/|website=SF Gate|publisher=San Francisco Gate|accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> The Good Food Awards have been particularly notable in the coffee industry.<ref name=Brown>{{cite web|last1=Brown|first1=Nick|title=The Good Food Awards: How it Works, How to Win, and Coffee ‘Elitism’|url=http://dailycoffeenews.com/2014/01/20/the-good-food-awards-how-it-works-how-to-win-and-coffee-elitism/|website=Daily Coffee News|publisher=Roast Magazine|accessdate=24 June 2015}}</ref> As of the 2018 Good Food Awards, [[Patric Chocolate]] has won twenty-one awards, more than any other entrant.
==Criteria== The criteria for the Good Food Awards varies by industry, however basic rules says that entries must be made without GM ingredients, using good animal husbandry and "without the use of artificial ingredients, hormones, synthetic pesticides, herbicides, fertilizer " and, most importantly, crafted in the USA.
